Example life table

exampleLT.Rd

Example death count and population values. Also includes mx (deaths / population), and ax and qx calculated using functions from this package.

exampleLT

Format

A data.table with columns:

age_start

Integer, abridged ages 0, 1, 5, 10, ..., 95

age_end

Integer, end of age group inclusive, 1, 5, 10, ... , 95, Inf

deaths

Death counts

population

Population counts

mx

mortality rate (deaths / population)

ax

mean person-years lived by those who die in interval. Obtained using mx_to_ax function.

qx

probability of death in interval conditional on survival to xth birthday. Obtained using mx_ax_to_qx function.
